    <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Collection of Persian poetry with an introductory table of contents by Saʻīd Nafīsī, a former owner (p.1). Several leaves copied by Nafīsī and inserted. They include two poems by Ḥāfiẓ (p. 156); 12 pages containing poems from the margins of a copy of Khusraw Dihlavī (p.197b-197l); and two poems missing from the Dīvān of Ḥakīm Tirmiz̲ī (unnumbered page after p. 259).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="546" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Persian.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Title supplied by cataloger; titles of component parts from table of contents (p. 1).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">1. p. 1-29: Ghazalīyāt-i Khusraw Dihlavī -- 2. p. 30-60: Ghazalīyāt-i Ḥāfiẓ Shīrāzī -- 3. p. 61-155:  Ashʻār-i Salmān Sāvajī -- 4. p. 125-157: [Ghazalīyāt] -- 5. p. 157-197: Dīvān-i Bisāṭī Samarqandī -- 6. p. 199-229: Ashʻār-i Fakhr al-Dīn Ibrāhīm ʻIrāqī -- 7. p. 230-240: Lamaʻāt-i Fakhr al-Dīn Ibrāhīm ʻIrāqī --8. p. 241-253: Tarkībʹband va ashʻār-i dīgar-i ʻIrāqī -- 9. p. 254-259: Muqaṭṭaʻāt-i Ibn Yamīn -- 10 . p. 260-304: Ashʻār-i Ḥakīm Tirmiz̲ī -- 11 p. 305-323: Fī bayān-i munāẓirah-ʼi al-Aṭʻimah -- 12. p. 325-345: Muntakhab-i mas̲navīyāt-i Khusraw Dihlavī va Niẓāmī.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="530" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Also available as a digital facsimile.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: 21 long lines; chiefly in two columns; no catchwords; border-ruled.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed; headings in thuluth; pointed and vocalized.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Illuminated headpiece in gold and colors (p. 61, 199); polychrome illuminated headers with leaf and vine motifs (p. 1, 125, 157, 305); textblock border-ruled in blue and red or blue and gold; columns and sections ruled in red; rubrications in red, green, blue, gold; some poetry set off by red markers.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: Copy completed in Muḥarram 836 AH (1432 CE) by ʻAlī ibn Ḥakīm Tirmiz̲ī (p. 240).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Shelfmark: MS Or 452.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="541" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Forms part of the Saʻīd Nafīsī collection purchased by Columbia Unversity in 1961 (library bookplate inside back cover).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="561" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Sold by Mīrzā ʻAlī Aṣghar Kitābfurūsh [bookseller] to Saʻīd Nafīsī in Tehran in Ābān 1314 (October 1935 CE) (note in ink, p. 200 [=0])</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="561" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Formerly owned by Saʻīd Nafīsī, number 3494 (stamp and note in ink, p. 200 [=0])</subfield>
